WEBVTT

00:00.882 --> 00:03.632
♪ dramatic music ♪

00:03.715 --> 00:05.757
[Ray] Previously
on  Ray Donovan...

00:05.840 --> 00:10.757
♪♪♪

00:16.299 --> 00:19.632
[Taser firing, crackling]

00:19.715 --> 00:24.799
♪♪♪

00:28.299 --> 00:29.049
[tires screech, glass shatters]

00:29.132 --> 00:29.966
[Bunchy grunts]

00:30.049 --> 00:35.216
♪♪♪

00:35.299 --> 00:36.424
[Ray] Give me
the fucking money, Bunch.

00:37.091 --> 00:38.424
[groans]

00:38.508 --> 00:40.383
[groaning] No!

00:40.466 --> 00:41.383
[Anita] Hey, stop that!

00:41.466 --> 00:42.882
Get off her!

00:42.966 --> 00:47.799
♪♪♪

00:52.383 --> 00:54.007
[shower running]

00:54.091 --> 00:57.424
♪♪♪

00:57.508 --> 01:01.424
[crowd yelling]

01:01.508 --> 01:06.674
♪♪♪

01:06.757 --> 01:09.924
[Bridget] If I want to be
happy, I have to move away.

01:10.007 --> 01:14.840
♪♪♪

01:22.508 --> 01:25.007
[camera shutters clicking]

01:25.091 --> 01:30.258
♪♪♪

01:31.590 --> 01:34.091
You don't look so good.

01:34.174 --> 01:39.007
[choking]

01:39.091 --> 01:40.549
[grunting]

01:40.632 --> 01:42.299
Dude! Stop!

01:42.383 --> 01:46.882
♪♪♪

01:53.757 --> 01:56.674
♪ angelic music ♪

01:56.757 --> 02:01.882
♪♪♪

02:08.799 --> 02:12.007
[Abby, echoing] Ray.

02:12.091 --> 02:17.007
♪♪♪

02:32.049 --> 02:34.924
[water splashes]

02:39.007 --> 02:42.424
Ray.

02:42.508 --> 02:45.383
[lights buzzing softly]

02:50.757 --> 02:52.757
[Amiot] Do you go by Raymond
or Ray?

02:58.341 --> 03:00.049
Ray.

03:00.132 --> 03:04.174
Okay, Ray.
I'm Dr. Amiot.

03:04.258 --> 03:06.799
Look straight ahead
for me, okay?

03:11.132 --> 03:13.590
Follow my index finger.

03:16.258 --> 03:18.549
Are you on any medications,
other than the sedative

03:18.632 --> 03:19.924
we gave you last night?

03:20.007 --> 03:21.632
No.

03:23.132 --> 03:24.882
Yeah, you don't need these.

03:24.966 --> 03:26.424
[straps click, Velcro rips]

03:38.590 --> 03:40.882
You're not gonna hit me,
are you, Ray?

03:40.966 --> 03:43.007
[groans softly]

03:45.715 --> 03:48.174
So what happened last night?

03:50.424 --> 03:52.007
I don't know.

03:52.091 --> 03:55.882
I just...forgot to eat
or something.

03:55.966 --> 03:57.924
Forgot to eat?

03:58.007 --> 03:59.674
Okay.

03:59.757 --> 04:02.632
[boy vocalizing softly]

04:15.091 --> 04:16.840
[Amiot]
What were we talking about?

04:16.924 --> 04:19.549
Oh, yeah. Yeah.
Last night.

04:21.840 --> 04:23.466
Did anything
out of the ordinary happen

04:23.549 --> 04:24.882
besides not eating?

04:24.966 --> 04:27.882
How long do I have to be here?

04:27.966 --> 04:31.799
You're being held under
my supervision for 72 hours.

04:31.882 --> 04:33.216
Mm.

04:35.966 --> 04:37.674
You ever been
in therapy, Ray?

04:37.757 --> 04:39.674
Yeah.

04:39.757 --> 04:42.341
- When was that?
- Last year.

04:42.424 --> 04:45.091
What was that like?
Did it...did it help?

04:45.174 --> 04:48.549
I don't know.
Anger management.

04:48.632 --> 04:51.258
- Oh. Yeah.
- Court-ordered.

04:51.341 --> 04:53.091
I don't believe
in court-ordered therapy.

04:53.174 --> 04:55.590
I think it's a total waste
of time.

04:55.674 --> 04:57.049
You have to be willing
to be helped.

04:57.132 --> 04:59.466
You know, you-you have to be
so uncomfortable

04:59.590 --> 05:03.715
or so...so much in pain

05:03.799 --> 05:05.508
that you're truly willing
to be helped.

05:05.590 --> 05:07.757
That's--I mean, that's what
I think. What do you think?

05:11.216 --> 05:12.924
When's the last time you ate?

05:15.757 --> 05:16.924
I don't know.

05:19.632 --> 05:21.466
Egg salad.

05:21.549 --> 05:23.383
My wife's recipe.

05:23.466 --> 05:24.882
The best in all of New York.

05:24.966 --> 05:26.466
Everybody said so.

05:26.549 --> 05:29.341
Here, try it.

05:29.424 --> 05:31.174
Try it.

05:37.216 --> 05:38.924
[groans softly]

05:43.924 --> 05:45.549
So?

05:48.258 --> 05:49.590
Uh-huh.

05:49.674 --> 05:50.799
My egg salad's
not nearly as good

05:50.882 --> 05:52.549
as my wife's.

05:52.632 --> 05:55.466
She had this special way
of measuring the mayonnaise.

05:55.549 --> 06:00.424
And she cut the celery
into these tiny, tiny slices.

06:04.007 --> 06:05.882
You married, Ray?

06:05.966 --> 06:08.715
No.

06:08.799 --> 06:11.966
So the ring is just to keep
the ladies away or what?

06:12.049 --> 06:14.091
She died.

06:14.174 --> 06:16.049
She must have been young.

06:17.924 --> 06:20.966
My wife was 81 when she died.

06:23.007 --> 06:25.632
She would have liked you.

06:25.715 --> 06:29.174
She was a music teacher.
She loved pauses.

06:30.715 --> 06:34.216
You know, the music
between the notes.

06:34.299 --> 06:36.007
The silence.

06:41.216 --> 06:43.590
Think you can tell me
what happened last night?

06:54.799 --> 06:57.632
Sometimes I get overwhelmed.

06:57.715 --> 06:59.590
What's that like?

06:59.674 --> 07:01.091
Like I can't breathe.

07:01.174 --> 07:03.466
[breathes slowly]

07:03.549 --> 07:05.632
♪ somber music ♪

07:05.715 --> 07:07.632
Like I'm drowning.

07:09.840 --> 07:11.882
Is that what happened
last night?

07:14.174 --> 07:16.216
That happen a lot?

07:16.299 --> 07:21.174
♪♪♪

07:22.132 --> 07:23.715
Don't I get a phone call
or something?

07:23.799 --> 07:28.216
♪♪♪

07:28.299 --> 07:30.258
Is there anybody
you want me to contact?

07:30.341 --> 07:32.674
Yeah, a friend of mine.

07:32.757 --> 07:35.715
Has to be family.

07:35.799 --> 07:38.424
I'll get Andrew to come in
and get numbers.

07:38.508 --> 07:40.549
Be back later.

07:40.632 --> 07:45.508
♪♪♪

07:47.549 --> 07:49.549
[woman over TV] Take a look
at what's happening.

07:49.632 --> 07:52.299
...be a mostly clear,
beautiful, crisp day today.

07:52.383 --> 07:53.757
Most of those showers
heading

07:53.840 --> 07:57.091
towards the east
and Long Island.

07:57.174 --> 07:59.299
[man] Your turn.

07:59.383 --> 08:01.007
[woman over TV] Gusty winds
across the Big Apple

08:01.091 --> 08:02.674
this afternoon
as that cold front

08:02.757 --> 08:04.132
sweeps over the region.

08:04.216 --> 08:06.091
Fifty-eight degrees
is our high,

08:06.174 --> 08:08.715
and we have some
partly cloudy skies.

08:08.799 --> 08:12.258
Temperatures are decreasing
as the week goes on, however.

08:12.341 --> 08:14.341
You seen
my brother around?

08:14.424 --> 08:15.549
Who?

08:15.632 --> 08:16.924
Eldridge.

08:17.007 --> 08:19.966
He's my identical twin.

08:20.049 --> 08:23.341
We're about the same height.
Same color.

08:23.424 --> 08:26.132
We used to sit back-to-back,
and, without looking,

08:26.216 --> 08:30.590
we could draw the same thing.

08:30.674 --> 08:32.091
But I can't find him no more.

08:32.174 --> 08:33.715
[woman over TV]
Traveling this weekend,

08:33.799 --> 08:35.840
please take precaution
and allow yourself

08:35.924 --> 08:40.715
some extra time out there
on the roadways.

08:40.799 --> 08:43.174
Temperatures in the 30s
and 40s

08:43.258 --> 08:45.966
with a few clouds overhead.

08:46.049 --> 08:47.799
Now back to you, Sandy.

08:47.882 --> 08:49.007
[Sandy] Firefighters
responded...

08:49.091 --> 08:50.383
[Ptolomy] Don't do it.

08:50.466 --> 08:51.757
What?

08:51.840 --> 08:54.174
Don't drink
from the fountain.

08:54.258 --> 08:56.299
Why not?

08:56.383 --> 08:59.840
It's full of bromide.
It's how they sedate us.

08:59.924 --> 09:02.757
Helps them keep order.

09:02.840 --> 09:04.549
Drink from the toilet.

09:04.632 --> 09:08.299
[newscaster continues
indistinctly]

09:13.757 --> 09:15.590
Visiting time.

09:15.674 --> 09:18.840
If you hear your name called,
that means you have a visitor.

09:18.924 --> 09:20.632
Go to the psych-tech station,
and you will receive

09:20.715 --> 09:22.966
your visitor's badge.

09:23.049 --> 09:25.007
Aaron Burch, Raymond Donovan,

09:25.091 --> 09:27.299
Ronald Lopez, Davanish Kher.

09:28.882 --> 09:30.632
The psych tech will hand you
your visitor's badge.

09:30.715 --> 09:32.341
One at a time.

09:36.715 --> 09:38.174
You seen Eldridge?

09:38.258 --> 09:39.757
I didn't call your name.
Please sit down.

09:39.840 --> 09:41.258
Well, maybe you can
look again.

09:41.341 --> 09:43.174
I mean, maybe my brother's name
is on there.

09:44.632 --> 09:46.966
People get us confused.

09:50.341 --> 09:53.216
[indistinct chatter]

09:59.299 --> 10:00.757
[Andrew] Come on, Mr. Donovan.

10:00.840 --> 10:03.341
You only got 20 minutes.

10:09.882 --> 10:11.882
Hey, sweetheart.
How are you?

10:17.299 --> 10:19.049
[sighs]

10:22.924 --> 10:24.674
What happened?

10:26.674 --> 10:28.299
It's a misunderstanding.

10:28.383 --> 10:30.174
They wouldn't tell me
anything on the phone.

10:30.258 --> 10:34.174
Just, uh, I forgot to eat,
you know.

10:34.258 --> 10:36.882
- Are you okay?
- Sure, just got...

10:36.966 --> 10:39.840
got dizzy, and I passed out.

10:39.924 --> 10:42.091
You got dizzy
and passed out

10:42.174 --> 10:44.216
and they brought you
to a psych ward?

10:49.383 --> 10:51.674
Sweetheart, I need you
to call someone for me.

10:51.757 --> 10:53.258
Wh-who?

10:53.341 --> 10:54.882
A friend.
His name is Sean McGrath.

10:54.966 --> 10:56.216
I want you to write down
his number for me.

10:56.299 --> 10:59.049
- Who is he?
- He's a cop. He can help.

11:01.383 --> 11:04.466
Dad, look at me.
What happened?

11:04.549 --> 11:06.341
I just need you to get
a message to him.

11:06.424 --> 11:08.341
I just need you to tell him
I'm here

11:08.424 --> 11:10.091
- and he needs to come--
- Tell him you forgot to eat--

11:10.174 --> 11:12.715
Are you gonna fucking
help me or not?

11:12.799 --> 11:15.799
♪ solemn music ♪

11:15.882 --> 11:20.757
♪♪♪

11:23.799 --> 11:25.466
[softly] I'm sorry.

11:25.549 --> 11:28.466
[crying softly]

11:28.549 --> 11:33.424
♪♪♪

11:37.174 --> 11:39.549
I'm in a tight spot here,
Bridge.

11:41.424 --> 11:43.715
I need you to get me
out of here.

11:43.799 --> 11:48.924
♪♪♪

11:52.757 --> 11:54.091
[sniffles]

11:54.174 --> 11:56.299
What's his number?

11:57.424 --> 12:02.508
♪♪♪

12:05.799 --> 12:07.091
[sniffles]

12:09.840 --> 12:11.424
[cell phone beeps]

12:11.508 --> 12:13.549
[cell phone ringing]

12:13.632 --> 12:15.258
Hello?

12:15.341 --> 12:16.715
[Bridget]
Is this Mr. McGrath?

12:16.799 --> 12:18.590
Who gave you this number?

12:18.674 --> 12:22.132
My name's Bridget Donovan.
My father is Ray Donovan.

12:22.216 --> 12:25.341
[Mac] Uh, Bridget, yeah.
Uh, hey.

12:26.383 --> 12:28.258
How do you know my dad?

12:28.341 --> 12:30.508
Uh, he lived in my father's
house for a while.

12:30.590 --> 12:32.132
[Bridget] On Staten Island?

12:32.216 --> 12:33.424
That's right.

12:33.508 --> 12:35.924
I didn't know that.

12:36.007 --> 12:37.674
[Mac] So what can I do
for you, Bridget?

12:39.424 --> 12:41.216
Bridget, you there?

12:42.882 --> 12:47.049
My father is in Grandview
in the psychiatric ward.

12:47.132 --> 12:49.466
What happened?

12:49.549 --> 12:51.508
The doctor said something
about a panic attack.

12:51.590 --> 12:55.216
Okay, was he...was he arrested,
or was he 5150'd?

12:55.299 --> 12:57.466
I don't know what that means.

12:57.549 --> 12:58.882
Y-you know what?
Don't worry about it.

12:58.966 --> 13:00.091
I'll figure it out.

13:00.174 --> 13:01.383
Uh, thanks for the call,
Bridget.

13:01.466 --> 13:03.966
[Bridget] Mr. McGrath?

13:04.049 --> 13:06.174
Where did you meet my dad?

13:06.258 --> 13:08.757
[Mac] Bridget, look, uh,
I gotta take care of this.

13:08.840 --> 13:11.549
But, uh, you did the right
thing calling me, okay?

13:11.632 --> 13:12.424
[cell phone clicks]

13:12.508 --> 13:13.632
[line clicks]

13:14.715 --> 13:16.132
- [cell phone beeps]
- [sniffles]

13:16.216 --> 13:18.132
Fuck.

13:18.216 --> 13:20.757
[line rings]

13:20.840 --> 13:23.466
Barry. Look, I got a friend
in Grandview, okay?

13:23.549 --> 13:25.799
I need him out,
like, yesterday.

13:25.882 --> 13:27.590
Yeah, I'll vouch.

13:27.674 --> 13:29.258
Donovan. Raymond Donovan.

13:29.341 --> 13:31.799
Picked up last night.
I owe you.

13:31.882 --> 13:34.799
[mystical music
playing over speakers]

13:34.882 --> 13:39.757
♪♪♪

13:48.715 --> 13:50.424
What's going on?

13:50.508 --> 13:53.258
I just talked to Scholl.
Feratti shut it down.

13:53.341 --> 13:55.258
- What?
- Feratti shut it down.

13:55.341 --> 13:57.216
He's fucking furious,
blames us.

13:57.299 --> 13:59.299
Says we're-we're
fucking sloppy.

13:59.383 --> 14:01.549
And I just bought
two goddamn Jet Skis,

14:01.632 --> 14:03.299
black one for me
and a pink one for Ally.

14:03.383 --> 14:05.549
Shut the fuck up, Danny.
Jesus fuck.

14:05.632 --> 14:07.632
Jet Skis? What is this,
a fucking game show?

14:13.174 --> 14:14.632
Scholl says it's IA.

14:14.715 --> 14:17.799
He's fucking paranoid,
thinks there's a rat.

14:17.882 --> 14:19.466
Why?

14:19.549 --> 14:21.715
He thinks someone
got paid off.

14:21.799 --> 14:24.049
He thinks that rich cunt
Winslow got to someone.

14:24.132 --> 14:26.299
- There ain't no fucking rat.
- That's what I said.

14:26.383 --> 14:29.049
But for the foreseeable,
we're done.

14:29.132 --> 14:31.840
It's just because
of the election. He's spooked.

14:31.924 --> 14:33.216
He'll pick it up again
afterwards.

14:33.299 --> 14:36.258
Fuck that.
If it's IA...

14:36.341 --> 14:38.924
I'm gonna find out
who the fuck it is.

14:39.007 --> 14:43.966
♪♪♪

14:50.132 --> 14:52.549
[sighs]

14:52.632 --> 14:55.966
I already told Ally
I got the goddamn things.

14:56.049 --> 14:57.341
Think I can return 'em

14:57.424 --> 14:59.674
if I haven't put 'em
in the water yet?

15:03.757 --> 15:05.840
[cell phone ringing]

15:09.424 --> 15:10.424
[cell phone clicks]

15:10.508 --> 15:11.590
Bridge?

15:11.674 --> 15:13.882
My dad had a panic attack,

15:13.966 --> 15:16.590
and he's in Grandview,
and they won't let him out.

15:17.966 --> 15:18.924
Yeah?

15:21.840 --> 15:25.299
He made me call some guy
to come get him.

15:25.383 --> 15:28.632
I don't know why he didn't
just ask me to call you.

15:29.882 --> 15:31.341
All right, where are you?

15:31.424 --> 15:33.341
[Bridget]
Still at the hospital.

15:37.424 --> 15:39.882
- Lena?
- Yeah, um...

15:41.383 --> 15:43.508
I-I'll be there soon, okay?

15:46.007 --> 15:46.674
[cell phone beeps]

15:47.715 --> 15:49.757
Yo, Sandy, I need a towel!

15:49.840 --> 15:51.299
What?

15:51.383 --> 15:53.299
I said I need a towel!

15:53.383 --> 15:54.799
[sighs]

15:56.091 --> 15:58.132
I'm coming!

16:00.299 --> 16:02.383
Oh.

16:02.466 --> 16:04.508
Did you say something?

16:04.590 --> 16:06.049
Yeah, I need a towel.

16:06.132 --> 16:07.341
I'm, like, dripping wet here
and making a mess.

16:07.424 --> 16:10.590
[chuckles] I didn't hear you.

16:13.549 --> 16:16.258
Oh, of course.

16:16.341 --> 16:18.091
A towel.

16:23.091 --> 16:24.132
Can I help you?

16:24.216 --> 16:26.632
No, I'm good.
Thanks.

16:26.715 --> 16:29.049
Hey, uh, I noticed you got
some real quality equipment

16:29.132 --> 16:31.091
- right there.
- Oh, that.

16:31.174 --> 16:33.508
I had a racket going
for a while

16:33.590 --> 16:36.258
for seniors, uh, when they
had trouble hearing.

16:36.341 --> 16:38.424
- Uh-huh.
- And so I would record

16:38.508 --> 16:39.966
the good book for them.

16:40.049 --> 16:41.966
It was soothing.

16:42.049 --> 16:43.966
You mean trouble seeing.

16:44.049 --> 16:45.840
No, hearing.

16:45.924 --> 16:48.383
I would read it really loud.

16:48.466 --> 16:51.508
I got a voice that carries.

16:51.590 --> 16:54.049
Yeah.

16:54.132 --> 16:55.715
Yeah.

16:55.799 --> 16:57.258
Mm.

16:57.341 --> 16:59.299
♪ dramatic music ♪

16:59.383 --> 17:02.299
[indistinct speech over TV]

17:02.383 --> 17:05.466
[cell phone clicking]

17:05.549 --> 17:08.466
[cell phone ringing
and buzzing]

17:08.549 --> 17:13.632
♪♪♪

17:14.132 --> 17:16.799
[ringing and buzzing continue]

17:16.882 --> 17:19.757
[breathing shakily]

17:21.757 --> 17:24.299
[line ringing]

17:24.383 --> 17:26.174
[Terry] This is Terry Donovan.
Leave a message.

17:26.258 --> 17:27.632
[beep]

17:27.715 --> 17:30.966
♪♪♪

17:31.049 --> 17:31.924
[cell phone clicks]

17:33.549 --> 17:36.549
Test. Testing.

17:36.632 --> 17:37.882
Mm-hmm.

17:37.966 --> 17:40.383
How did your song go?

17:40.466 --> 17:42.049
What, you wanna hear it?

17:42.132 --> 17:44.174
I do, very much.

17:44.258 --> 17:48.299
[tape recorder humming]

17:48.383 --> 17:50.299
♪ Girl ♪

17:50.383 --> 17:52.966
♪ It's the first thing
in the morning ♪

17:53.049 --> 17:55.966
♪ And I'm thinking
about your sweet thing ♪

17:56.049 --> 18:00.299
♪ And it's got me
feeling high ♪

18:00.383 --> 18:02.924
♪ Last night,
I saw you dancing ♪

18:03.007 --> 18:05.299
♪ Girl, I love your pants
and ♪

18:05.383 --> 18:07.424
♪ Come on, come on,
come on-- ♪

18:08.590 --> 18:10.757
What the fuck, Mick?
You just ruined my take.

18:10.840 --> 18:12.924
You've been to Ray's place
in the city, right?

18:13.007 --> 18:16.091
- Yeah. So?
- Give me his address, Daryll.

18:16.174 --> 18:18.174
Pop, you think you're just
gonna roll up to Ray's crib

18:18.258 --> 18:19.924
and knock on his door and
he'll give you the money back?

18:20.007 --> 18:22.966
Hey. Enough is enough.

18:23.049 --> 18:25.174
We need to have a serious
fucking conversation.

18:25.258 --> 18:26.341
Give me his address.

18:26.424 --> 18:27.966
[pen clatters]

18:28.049 --> 18:30.882
[woman vocalizing faintly]

18:47.174 --> 18:48.715
You've been released.

18:48.799 --> 18:50.882
Just got the order.

18:51.590 --> 18:53.216
How'd you pull that off?

18:55.216 --> 18:57.840
Somebody made a call for me.

18:57.924 --> 19:00.216
Who?

19:00.299 --> 19:01.840
Doesn't matter.

19:09.882 --> 19:13.840
Look, I've got no dog
in this fight,

19:13.924 --> 19:16.466
but I don't think
you should leave, not yet.

19:16.549 --> 19:18.383
I know this isn't
the Four Seasons,

19:18.466 --> 19:19.757
but in your situation,
it's good to get

19:19.840 --> 19:22.424
a real break
from everything.

19:22.508 --> 19:24.757
Get yourself reoriented.

19:26.174 --> 19:28.341
I'm fine.

19:28.424 --> 19:30.590
You blacked out last night.

19:31.799 --> 19:33.590
You attacked a policeman.

19:36.049 --> 19:38.799
You really think
that qualifies as fine?

19:45.632 --> 19:46.799
Okay.

19:48.466 --> 19:51.174
Sometimes I see people
privately in my apartment.

19:51.258 --> 19:54.132
I answer my own phone.

19:54.216 --> 19:57.799
Next time you forget to eat,
give me a call.

20:06.383 --> 20:07.632
[knock at door]

20:11.966 --> 20:13.966
You leave your door open?

20:15.508 --> 20:17.383
What are you doing here?

20:19.966 --> 20:21.632
I missed you, son.

20:22.799 --> 20:24.590
Cut the bullshit.

20:24.674 --> 20:26.091
What do you want?

20:27.466 --> 20:29.091
Who beat you up?

20:29.174 --> 20:31.424
