you should know about.

23:49.341 --> 23:53.466
It's stuff that no one's
gonna tell you.

23:53.549 --> 23:56.383
[siren wailing distantly]

23:59.299 --> 24:02.049
[sighs]
I gotta go, Bridge.

24:02.132 --> 24:04.174
Wait, no, no, no.
Hold on a second.

24:05.715 --> 24:07.508
What don't I know?

24:11.424 --> 24:12.840
Tell her.

24:16.383 --> 24:18.799
Come on. Tell her why
you were in Staten Island.

24:23.216 --> 24:25.007
What is she talking about?

24:26.590 --> 24:29.341
Tell her what you did
two months ago.

24:32.549 --> 24:34.341
Dad?

24:36.258 --> 24:39.424
He jumped off a fucking
building into the East River.

24:39.508 --> 24:41.715
And that cop you called
saved his life.

24:41.799 --> 24:46.132
♪ somber music ♪

24:46.216 --> 24:49.174
Jesus. Just be
fucking honest for once.

24:51.007 --> 24:53.258
Is that true?

24:55.966 --> 24:57.882
My name is Eldridge Damascus.

24:57.966 --> 24:59.549
I'm here to see
my brother, Demar.

24:59.632 --> 25:03.091
What about Conor?
You're all he has left.

25:05.258 --> 25:07.424
What about me?

25:07.508 --> 25:11.757
♪♪♪

25:11.840 --> 25:13.299
I'm sorry.

25:14.799 --> 25:16.799
Dad, you're sick.

25:16.882 --> 25:18.882
You need help.

25:22.049 --> 25:24.549
You should stay here.

25:27.632 --> 25:29.882
I gotta go, sweetheart.

25:29.966 --> 25:35.091
♪♪♪

25:38.049 --> 25:39.466
Hey.

25:40.840 --> 25:42.882
[clears throat] Ray.

25:44.632 --> 25:46.424
We got a problem.

25:46.508 --> 25:48.258
Feratti knows there's
an IA investigation.

25:48.341 --> 25:50.674
He knows someone's
wearing a wire.

25:50.757 --> 25:52.049
They're gonna shut down
the prison scam.

25:52.132 --> 25:54.590
They're all pissed.

25:54.674 --> 25:57.383
They're gonna figure out
who Emerson Lake is.

25:57.466 --> 25:59.840
Feratti has too many people
on the inside.

25:59.924 --> 26:01.590
They're gonna figure out
Emerson.

26:01.674 --> 26:04.799
Emerson's gonna lead them
to me, then to you.

26:04.882 --> 26:07.216
You hear me, Ray?

26:07.299 --> 26:09.924
This is gonna lead
straight to you.

26:12.091 --> 26:14.258
We gotta kill Emerson Lake.

26:14.341 --> 26:17.383
- No.
- Oh, really, Ray?

26:17.466 --> 26:19.383
Then what the fuck
are we gonna do?

26:19.466 --> 26:21.674
- Go home.
- What?

26:21.757 --> 26:23.508
I'll take care of it.

26:23.590 --> 26:28.508
♪♪♪

26:33.757 --> 26:36.383
[water bubbling]

26:36.466 --> 26:39.341
[coughing]

26:41.674 --> 26:44.383
[breathes slowly]

26:47.674 --> 26:50.715
Fucking knew you were
fighting again.

26:50.799 --> 26:52.174
Yeah, it's true.

26:52.258 --> 26:55.258
[chuckles] Jesus,
you're high as fuck.

26:55.341 --> 26:58.091
[chuckles] I am.

26:58.174 --> 27:00.466
[Bunchy] You look like hell.

27:00.549 --> 27:02.299
I do?

27:04.383 --> 27:06.882
You know, if you get
in the ring like that,

27:06.966 --> 27:08.799
you're gonna get
your fucking ass kicked.

27:10.091 --> 27:11.715
No shit.

27:15.924 --> 27:18.258
So let me take your place.

27:47.966 --> 27:49.924
[door buzzes, lock clicks]

27:50.007 --> 27:51.757
Alley's closed.

27:51.840 --> 27:53.174
I'm here to see Feratti.

27:53.258 --> 27:54.799
Who?

27:54.882 --> 27:56.424
The mayor.

27:57.799 --> 27:59.341
Tell him Ray Donovan's here.

27:59.424 --> 28:00.799
He'll want to hear
what I have to say.

28:04.424 --> 28:07.299
[crows cawing]

28:10.091 --> 28:12.674
[man] Used to be pigeons
out here.

28:12.757 --> 28:14.299
Then the crows moved in.

28:16.924 --> 28:18.549
Crows eat pigeon eggs.

28:21.007 --> 28:22.299
[man] After you.

28:32.466 --> 28:34.424
- Stop.
- Turn around.

28:36.132 --> 28:37.924
Put your arms out.

28:48.049 --> 28:50.216
Your pants.

28:50.299 --> 28:52.924
- What?
- Take off your pants.

28:55.424 --> 28:57.174
[Ray sighs]

29:04.674 --> 29:07.424
All right, pick 'em up.

29:25.715 --> 29:29.715
Can I get you anything?
A drink, uh, coffee?

29:31.049 --> 29:32.383
No.

29:36.466 --> 29:39.383
[chuckles] What's on your mind,
Mr. Donovan?

29:42.341 --> 29:45.424
You got an IA problem.

29:45.508 --> 29:47.424
That's news to me.

29:47.508 --> 29:48.966
What, that there's
an investigation

29:49.049 --> 29:50.840
or that they're talking
to someone?

29:50.924 --> 29:53.174
Thought you worked
for Sam Winslow.

29:53.258 --> 29:54.840
She replaced me.

29:54.924 --> 29:56.258
Hmm.

29:56.341 --> 29:59.341
That dead girl yesterday...

29:59.424 --> 30:01.674
I'm assuming
that was Winslow's doing?

30:03.799 --> 30:06.049
I don't know anything
about that.

30:06.132 --> 30:08.049
Course you wouldn't.

30:10.174 --> 30:13.216
So what do you know,
Mr. Donovan?

30:13.299 --> 30:15.757
I know the IA guy
who's investigating you.

30:15.840 --> 30:17.216
Is that so?

30:17.299 --> 30:19.258
I could talk to him.

30:19.341 --> 30:20.840
Find out who his source is.

30:20.924 --> 30:23.882
And why would you do that?

30:23.966 --> 30:25.840
I got a brother.

30:27.299 --> 30:30.174
A little trouble with
the FBI, California.

30:30.258 --> 30:32.840
- Mm.
- Your reach extend that far?

30:32.924 --> 30:34.924
Mm-hmm.

30:37.508 --> 30:41.715
Would you give me the officer's
name as a good-faith gesture?

30:41.799 --> 30:43.715
I do that, you don't
need me anymore.

30:43.799 --> 30:46.299
Hmm.
Fair enough.

30:47.799 --> 30:50.007
You help my brother,

30:50.091 --> 30:52.799
I fix your IA problem.

30:54.258 --> 30:55.799
What would that entail?

30:57.299 --> 30:59.299
Whatever it takes.

30:59.383 --> 31:01.757
[chuckles softly]

31:01.840 --> 31:04.715
[cell phone ringing]

31:21.132 --> 31:22.299
[cell phone clicks]

31:22.383 --> 31:23.632
Yes?

31:23.715 --> 31:25.216
We need to talk.

31:25.299 --> 31:27.049
[Emerson] About what?

31:27.132 --> 31:28.840
Not on the phone.

31:31.007 --> 31:33.632
Square Diner, 20 minutes.

31:33.715 --> 31:34.632
[cell phone beeps]

31:37.007 --> 31:41.132
[soft pop music
playing over stereo]

31:41.216 --> 31:43.091
- Oh, hey, babe.
- Hey.

31:43.174 --> 31:45.549
I, uh, Zillowed a place
outside Philadelphia

31:45.632 --> 31:48.299
that I think you're
really gonna like.

31:48.383 --> 31:51.007
♪♪♪

31:51.091 --> 31:54.299
We...we can't go.

31:54.383 --> 31:58.299
♪♪♪

31:58.383 --> 32:00.674
- Uh, why?
- I know. I'm sorry.

32:00.757 --> 32:03.341
I know this is, like,
all my idea. I just...

32:05.007 --> 32:06.715
[sighs]

32:15.049 --> 32:18.174
The night of your surgery,

32:18.258 --> 32:21.132
my dad tried to kill himself.

32:21.216 --> 32:22.715
What?

32:22.799 --> 32:25.091
He jumped off a building
into the East River.

32:25.174 --> 32:26.715
And he lived?

32:28.632 --> 32:30.757
Well, yeah, I mean,
obviously, uh, he lived.

32:30.840 --> 32:33.590
- It-it's just--
- I just, like--I can't...

32:33.674 --> 32:35.632
like, leave him.

32:35.715 --> 32:37.216
He needs me.

32:48.966 --> 32:50.007
[chuckles]

32:50.091 --> 32:52.590
No, he doesn't.

32:54.715 --> 32:55.799
What?

32:55.882 --> 32:57.674
He doesn't need you.

32:59.258 --> 33:01.174
He's sick.

33:01.258 --> 33:05.632
Sure, he's-he's sick, but...

33:05.715 --> 33:07.674
is he gonna let you help him?

33:09.715 --> 33:13.091
- No.
- Then he doesn't need you.

33:13.174 --> 33:15.674
I don't know.

33:15.757 --> 33:17.508
I'm just like, "What the fuck?"
[sniffles]

33:17.590 --> 33:20.424
You know,
he-he's jumping off buildings

33:20.508 --> 33:24.091
and ending up at Grandview
with some cop.

33:24.174 --> 33:26.924
I just have a very bad feeling.

33:27.007 --> 33:29.258
If you have a bad feeling,
then we-we could just go.

33:31.508 --> 33:34.091
- I can't.
- [chuckles] The thing is...

33:34.174 --> 33:36.632
is, you can.

33:36.715 --> 33:40.840
You know, w-we don't need to be
around any of this anymore.

33:40.924 --> 33:43.799
I think that it's time
that we-we put him--

33:43.882 --> 33:47.091
we-we-we put all of this shit

33:47.174 --> 33:49.258
behind us and we just leave.

33:49.341 --> 33:51.882
We could go.
We could go now.

33:51.966 --> 33:54.632
We could go tonight.

33:54.715 --> 33:56.715
We don't have to look back.

33:58.341 --> 34:01.632
♪ dramatic music ♪

34:01.715 --> 34:02.966
[sniffles]

34:03.049 --> 34:08.216
♪♪♪

34:33.007 --> 34:34.299
What's this about?

34:34.383 --> 34:35.674
I talked to Feratti.

34:35.757 --> 34:37.216
You?

34:37.299 --> 34:39.341
He knows there's
an investigation.

34:39.424 --> 34:41.258
He knows you got
an informant.

34:41.341 --> 34:42.632
How does he know that?

34:42.715 --> 34:44.674
'Cause I told him.

34:44.757 --> 34:47.715
- You told him?
- Yeah.

34:47.799 --> 34:50.508
I need you to wire me
so I can go back in.

34:50.590 --> 34:53.132
- To do what?
- I gotta give him names.

34:53.216 --> 34:55.424
- Whose names?
- Yours and the informant's.

34:55.508 --> 34:57.674
Mine? You're fucking
out of your mind.

34:57.757 --> 34:59.549
He needs to think it's real.

34:59.632 --> 35:01.924
You name McGrath, he'll be dead
by the end of the day.

35:02.007 --> 35:03.799
So give me someone else.

35:03.882 --> 35:06.049
This is a real investigation,

35:06.132 --> 35:08.549
not some hide-the-hooker
Hollywood bullshit.

35:09.674 --> 35:11.674
Fine, suit yourself.

35:14.299 --> 35:15.924
Judge Scholl.

35:16.007 --> 35:17.966
What?

35:18.049 --> 35:21.383
- Judge R. Gregory Scholl.
- Who's that?

35:21.466 --> 35:24.341
He's a criminal court judge.
Richmond County.

35:24.424 --> 35:27.299
Sentences the homeless
and indigent to life plus 20

35:27.383 --> 35:30.508
while he's paying mortgages
on five properties.

35:30.590 --> 35:32.882
Likes cocaine
and sports betting.

35:32.966 --> 35:35.840
He's been all over Feratti
for a bigger skim.

35:37.341 --> 35:39.424
Why would he be
talking to you?

35:40.799 --> 35:43.383
Tell him Scholl got
in deep with a bookie,

35:43.466 --> 35:45.590
paroled one of his life
plus 20s on condition

35:45.674 --> 35:47.424
he broke the bookie's arm.

35:47.508 --> 35:48.966
Tell him the parolee
went too far

35:49.049 --> 35:51.424
and now Scholl's stooge
is facing a murder rap

35:51.508 --> 35:53.424
and is singing for IA.

35:53.508 --> 35:56.341
Tell him that's how I got him.

35:56.424 --> 35:57.924
Hey, it's a bizarre
enough story.

35:58.007 --> 35:59.715
Feratti just might bite.

36:01.424 --> 36:02.632
Where's the wire?

36:02.715 --> 36:04.091
Get in.

36:14.383 --> 36:17.007
When you met the mayor,
they had you undress, correct?

36:17.091 --> 36:18.216
Yeah.

36:18.299 --> 36:20.424
All right.

36:20.508 --> 36:22.757
You'll need to tape the
microphone to your perineum.

36:22.840 --> 36:25.632
- My what?
- Your perineum.

36:25.715 --> 36:29.258
The flat space between your
testicles and your asshole.

36:32.466 --> 36:35.091
One more thing.

36:35.174 --> 36:37.049
There's a hold back
per inmate.

36:37.132 --> 36:39.508
Ten percent, the prison budget
from the city.

36:39.590 --> 36:41.383
$68,000 per prisoner.

36:41.466 --> 36:43.674
Feratti actually budgets
$78,000.

36:43.757 --> 36:46.590
The other ten is split
between Feratti and Scholl.

36:46.674 --> 36:48.383
They're the only two
who know that.

36:48.466 --> 36:50.590
How do you know it?

36:50.674 --> 36:53.007
Let's say that Judge Scholl's
garbage continued

36:53.091 --> 36:55.632
to be collected during
our recent Sanitation strike.

37:03.632 --> 37:05.715
[engine turning over]

37:05.799 --> 37:07.299
Oh, and, Ray,

37:07.383 --> 37:08.549
when you're wearing the wire,

37:08.632 --> 37:10.341
try to maintain a wide stance.

37:10.424 --> 37:11.674
Helps with the audio.

37:17.924 --> 37:20.840
[indistinct chatter]

37:20.924 --> 37:21.840
[Mickey]
Fighter coming through.

37:21.924 --> 37:23.132
Fighter coming through.

37:23.840 --> 37:25.049
Fighter coming through.

37:25.132 --> 37:27.424
[Mickey speaking indistinctly]

37:27.508 --> 37:29.091
Right back in there.

37:36.632 --> 37:38.799
He's just a fucking
weight lifter.

37:40.216 --> 37:42.715
Shh!

37:42.799 --> 37:45.383
Terry Donovan has been
medically dejected

37:45.466 --> 37:47.049
from the eliminator.

37:47.132 --> 37:48.341
[crowd clamoring]

37:48.424 --> 37:49.840
[Big Easy] And in his place,

37:49.924 --> 37:53.299
a man experienced
in the arts of fistiana:

37:53.383 --> 37:55.091
El Trebol!

37:55.174 --> 37:56.341
[crowd jeering]

37:56.424 --> 37:58.882
[Big Easy]
Hey. [clapping]

38:00.216 --> 38:04.091
And we all know
Thomas The Iron Lung.

38:04.174 --> 38:07.049
[cheers and applause]

38:09.466 --> 38:10.341
[inhales sharply]

38:12.715 --> 38:14.049
[inhales sharply]

38:18.049 --> 38:21.049
Any doubt, you take a dive.

38:23.590 --> 38:28.383
[crowd clamoring]

38:28.466 --> 38:31.424
Hands up, Bunch.
Hands up.

38:31.508 --> 38:34.799
Jab! You first!

38:34.882 --> 38:37.299
Slip!

38:37.383 --> 38:38.299
You first.

38:38.383 --> 38:41.091
Jab! Jab! Slip!

38:41.174 --> 38:42.341
Slip!

38:43.174 --> 38:45.258
[grunting]

38:47.049 --> 38:48.549
Fuck.

38:48.632 --> 38:50.132
- [both grunting]
- [Terry] Hold him!

38:50.216 --> 38:51.132
Hold him!

38:51.216 --> 38:53.091
[crowd clamoring]

38:57.341 --> 38:58.299
Hold him!

38:58.383 --> 39:00.549
[yelling]

39:00.632 --> 39:02.924
[crowd yells]

39:04.882 --> 39:07.091
[Thomas grunting]

39:13.674 --> 39:16.341
[Thomas breathing hoarsely]

39:16.424 --> 39:19.299
♪ dark music ♪

39:19.383 --> 39:24.258
